dcterms:creator: Oriol Vinyals
Meire Fortunato
Navdeep Jaitly
dcterms:description: The Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP) aims to find the shortest possible route that visits a set of cities and returns to the origin city.
dcterms:title: Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP)

dcterms:creator: Mohammadreza Nazari
Afshin Oroojlooy
Lawrence Snyder
Martin Takác
dcterms:description: The Capacitated Vehicle Routing Problem (CVRP) is an extension of TSP that aims to find a set of routes for a fleet of vehicles to deliver goods to a set of customers while respecting capacity constraints.
dcterms:title: Capacitated Vehicle Routing Problem (CVRP)

dcterms:creator: Wouter Kool
Herke van Hoof
Max Welling
dcterms:description: The Prize Collecting TSP (PCTSP) is a variant of TSP where the goal is to find a tour that maximizes the total prize collected while minimizing the total distance traveled.
dcterms:title: Prize Collecting TSP (PCTSP)

dcterms:creator: Gorka Kobeaga
María Merino
Jose A Lozano
dcterms:description: The Orienteering Problem (OP) involves finding a tour that maximizes the total prize collected while adhering to a maximum tour length constraint.
dcterms:title: Orienteering Problem (OP)

dcterms:creator: Gerhard Reinelt
dcterms:description: TSPLIB is a library of sample instances for the Traveling Salesman Problem and related problems, providing a benchmark for evaluating algorithms.
dcterms:title: TSPLIB (for real-world TSP problems)
